{
  "id": "1953208290600315883",
  "title": "Full-Stack Web Development Team Needed to Build an E-Commerce Store from Scratch",
  "description": "Hi there, thank you for checking out my job post!\n\nWe're building a custom e-commerce platform inspired by boxed.gg and luxdrop.com. Users will purchase themed mystery boxes (shoes, streetwear, jewelry, etc.) and open them using a slot-machine-style animation to reveal randomized items.\n\nThis job is for Phase 1 — a fully functional MVP with the core user experience in place.\n\n✅ Scope of Work – MVP Features\n\n1. User Registration & Login\n- Email/password auth\n- JWT-based sessions\n- Dashboard showing balance and inventory\n\n2. Mystery Box Purchase Flow\n- Homepage with 1–2 boxes\n- Box detail page with price and description\n- “Open” button (requires enough credit)\n\n3. Slot-Style Unboxing Animation\n- Lightweight front-end animation (CSS or Canvas)\n- Randomized item reveal (based on predefined odds)\n- Item added to user inventory\n\n4. Store Credit / Wallet System\n- Track user balances\n- Adjust balance after purchase/sale\n- Add funds via Stripe (sandbox)\n\n5. Inventory Page\n- List of unboxed items\n- Option to sell items back for fixed credit (e.g. 70% of box cost)\n\n6. Basic Admin Panel\n- View users, balances, and inventories\n- Stats like total users, revenue, and credits in circulation\n\nDesign Note\n- No advanced custom UI work required\n- We’ll use a clean, responsive template\n- Focus is on working features, not polished visuals in this phase\n\n🚫 Not Included in This Phase \n- Physical item withdrawal or shipping\n- Multi-category browsing\n- Support ticket system\n- Provably fair or Web3 logic\n- Admin box builder\n- Custom UI design (we’ll use a clean template)\n\nPreferred Tech Stack\n- Frontend: React\n- Backend: Node.js with Express\n- Database: PostgreSQL or MongoDB\n- Stripe for payments\n\nShopify and no-code tools won’t work due to animation and wallet logic.\n\nBudget: $7000\nTimeline: 4-6 weeks\n\nLooking forward to your applications, thanks for reading!",
  "experienceLevel": "INTERMEDIATE",
